      • getArg

        protected java.lang.String getArg(java.lang.String argid)
        Attempt to retrieve an arg String value via our specific search chain. First try the command-line args directly for a match.
          arg=value
        If not found there try the the appropriate System property that would have been set on the command-line..
          -Dsafs.abbot.processcontainer.arg=value
        If not found there try looking for a stored value in the INI file.
        Returns:
        String value of the arg or null if the value was not found.

      • getBooleanArg

        protected boolean getBooleanArg(java.lang.String argid)
        Returns:
        true if arg String value equals ignoring case to "true". Any other String value will result in a return of false.
